Even with /n/ book-ciphers, there will be weak points, and they will
soon overlap. Forget about crypto for a moment, and just consider the
question of whether an effective random stream can be constructed by
mixing "books". The answer is clearly: Not!

Any decent crypto-PRNG beats such a stream, even when the individual
books have some true-random components. If you really have access to
some true-random shared information, but not enough to one-time pad
the whole message, mix it with the crypto-PRNG. The best way is to
re-key the cipher as frequently as possible given the message/pad
ratio.

Robert

